hash: 0000000327-d6e14b48c456b17b4319170961f954f0f0539c7fecb2960fcb6ca3249d4d096a
[Disable page numbers by default.
dburrows@debian.org**20050617214031
 On single-page resumes, it looks silly to have a
 lonely "1" down at the bottom of the resume.  You
 can turn page numbers back on using \pagestyle{normal}.
 If anyone can figure out how to disable page numbering
 iff the document has a single page, that would be
 absolutely wonderful (multi-pass solutions are ok).
] 
hash: 0000000462-879b34f28a094c06816f0b0e3125d9337ec8ffcdab5a6c4d2770942f43c924f8
[Extend vertical margins by default
dburrows@debian.org**20050617214208
 Modified the default page geometry of resumes to provide
 more vertical space for listing your MANY and VARIED
 accomplishments.  Yes, this was prompted by my resume
 becoming just a hair longer than one page.  This is
 done using the geometry package, so you should use the
 \geometry command to handle any additional geometry
 changes (like shrinking the margins to balance text
 between pages).
] 
